The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 December is 9,660 (1,118.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 December, there were 495 new confirmed cases (57.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 November, there were 580 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 15% (85 fewer cases).
